channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden Campaign Official Accuses Media of ‘Election Interference’ in Biden Debate Coverage
Bragg does 'not oppose' Trump request to delay sentencing; awaits Judge Merchan's approval
item.description: Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg told Judge Juan Merchan Tuesday that he does not oppose former President Trump's request to delay his sentencing scheduled for next week.

item.title: Manhattan DA's Office Won't Oppose Trump Filing Motion
item.description: Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg's office Tuesday said it will not oppose a request from President Donald Trump to file a motion that argues his felony conviction should be tossed in the wake of the Supreme Court's ruling on presidential immunity.

item.title: Grab the Popcorn: Tucker Reveals What 'Unusually Good Source' Shared About Obama/Biden Relationship
Arizona election worker charged in security-related thefts seen with Democrat politicians in resurfaced photos
item.description: A Maricopa County election worker charged in two thefts posted photos with Democratic politicians, including a U.S. senator and the leader of the Arizona Department of Public Safety.

item.title: Rep. Tenney to Newsmax: Obama Really Running Government
item.description: Rep. Claudia Tenney, R-N.Y., told Newsmax Tuesday that "Democrats don't care" about the physical and mental condition of President Joe Biden because he's merely a figurehead. Former President Barack Obama is really running the government, she said.

item.title: With Biden on the Ropes, Kamala Harris Further Collapses, Leaving Democrats Scrambling
How would a President Harris handle immigration, border crisis?
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris, should she replace President Biden, could continue a number of liberal policies while potentially going even further.

item.title: Rudy Giuliani Disbarred in New York
item.description: Rudy Giuliani lost his New York law license Tuesday.

item.title: Watergate Hero Carl Bernstein Confirms Biden’s Condition, Unintentionally Confirms Complicity to Hide It
Biden donors back 'Plan B', say 'it's Armageddon' after debate: reports
item.description: Donors reportedly are signaling they want to see a "Plan B" for the Democratic presidential nomination following President Biden's debate performance.

item.title: Suffolk Poll: Trump Leads Biden Nationwide After Debate
item.description: Former President Donald Trump gained the lead over President Joe Biden in the latest national poll of the 2024 candidates from Suffolk University and USA Today, conducted just after the first debate between the two of this election cycle.

item.title: Childless Disney Actress Gives Blisteringly Stupid Take About How Parents 'Overreach' When Raising Kids
Biden staff 'scared s---less' of him, senior admin official says; WH hits back
item.description: Staffers for President Biden are reportedly "scared s---less" by the commander in chief, due to years of aides and family members insulating him from outside input, according to a Politico report.

item.title: Experts: VP Harris May Get First Dibs on Biden's War Chest
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris is first in line to control of the tens of millions of dollars in President Joe Biden's campaign coffers if he decides to drop out of the 2024 race for the White House, according to his campaign manager, Julie Chavez Rodriguez.
